xmlData/document/body/p/0/r/t/__text: The Boston house-price data of Harrison, D. and Rubinfeld, D.L. 'Hedonic
xmlData/document/body/p/1/r/t/__text: prices and the demand for clean air', J. Environ. Economics & Management,
xmlData/document/body/p/2/r/t/__text: vol.5, 81-102, 1978.   Used in Belsley, Kuh & Welsch, 'Regression diagnostics
xmlData/document/body/p/3/r/t/__text: ...', Wiley, 1980.   N.B. Various transformations are used in the table on
xmlData/document/body/p/7/r/t/__text: CRIM     per capita crime rate by town
xmlData/document/body/p/8/r/t/__text: ZN       proportion of residential land zoned for lots over 25,000 sq.ft.
xmlData/document/body/p/9/r/t/__text: INDUS    proportion of non-retail business acres per town
xmlData/document/body/p/10/r/t/__text: CHAS     Charles River dummy variable (= 1 if tract bounds river; 0 otherwise)
xmlData/document/body/p/11/r/t/__text: NOX      nitric oxides concentration (parts per 10 million)
xmlData/document/body/p/12/r/t/__text: RM       average number of rooms per dwelling
xmlData/document/body/p/13/r/t/__text: AGE      proportion of owner-occupied units built prior to 1940
xmlData/document/body/p/14/r/t/__text: DIS      weighted distances to five Boston employment centres
xmlData/document/body/p/15/r/t/__text: RAD      index of accessibility to radial highways
xmlData/document/body/p/18/r/t/__text: B        1000(Bk - 0.63)^2 where Bk is the proportion of blacks by town
xmlData/document/body/p/19/r/t/__text: LSTAT    % lower status of the population
xmlData/document/body/p/20/r/t/__text: MEDV     Median value of owner-occupied homes in $1000's
